"v.修改，改进 无 n. 改进; v 改进 【参】mendicant(adj 乞丐的; n 乞丐)总是修补衣服; menial(adj 仆人的; n 仆人) 【反】rend(v 撕碎) 【记】同amend 修改；recommend 最值得推荐的精神是有错就改，人非圣贤，孰能无过？最值得推荐的是以后不再犯，有错则改 mend (v.)  c.1200, ""to repair,"" from a shortened form of Old French amender (see amend). Meaning ""to put right, atone for, amend (one's life), repent"" is from c.1300; that of ""to regain health"" is from early 15c. Related: Mended; mending. mend (n.)  early 14c., ""recompense, reparation,"" from mend (v.). Meaning ""act of mending; a repaired hole or rip in fabric"" is from 1888. Phrase on the mend attested from 1802."
